def get_floor_cat(row):
    floors_total = row['floors_total']
    floor = row['floor']
    
    try:
        if floor == 1:
            ret = ''
        elif floor == floors_total:
            ret = ''
        else:
            ret = ''
    except:
        ret = ''
    return ret

    total_area = row['total_area']
    living_area = row['living_area']

    except:
        ret = math.nan
    return ret

#    aggf -   (  - )
#    figsz -   (  - (10, 7))
def build_plot(df, x, y, titl, xlbl, aggf='mean', figsz=(10, 7)):
    df.pivot_table(
        index=x,
        values=y,
        aggfunc=aggf
    ).plot(
        title=titl,
        figsize=figsz,
        grid=True,
        style='o-',
        xlabel=xlbl
    )
    plt.show()

# #

          '    ', ' , ..')
